The purpose of this course is to provide school teachers (of any
subject, at all levels) with sufficient knowledge and background to
create interesting activities for their students making field trips to
the Honolulu Zoo.  The course will examine the Zoo's animal exhibits,
its botanical specimens, signs, print materials and personnel; and
will teach how to design a zoo excursion with educational value by
employing games, observations, group and individual activities and
other proven, field tested techniques.  For course information call
