EdCI 587K SEC. 1101 CRN 3094 PICD:SOCIAL SC -- TEACHING
AFRICAN-AMERICAN CULTURE IN HAWAIIAN PUBLIC SCHOOLS:  AN
INTERDISCIPLINARY APPROACH, GRADES 7-12 (1 cr)</strong><br>
This course is designed to expose secondary teachers in Hawai'i to an
overview of several disciplines from an African-American perspective. 
Teachers will emerge from the course with a better understanding of
this vital, over-looked part of American life and history, neglected
in education, while learning to utilize it as a tool for building
self-esteem in the youth of Hawai'i.  Additionally, teachers will gain
a better understanding of the cultural responses by African Americans
and Hawaiian-born people to their two histories, representing American
sub-cultures.
