crs)<br></strong>
This course is designed to prepare elementary and secondary teachers
to understand and implement peer-coaching and teacher support systems
in schools for continued instructional improvement.  Participants will
become familiar with some of the academic literature on this topic,
and with the practical techniques of peer coaching, including giving
feedback, conducting observations, and reflecting on their own
teaching.<br>
